var indicator_text = {
  "People above poverty": "<p>The <a href='https://www.census.gov/topics/income-poverty/poverty/guidance/poverty-measures.html' target='_blank'>poverty threshold</a> is a <a href='https://www.census.gov/topics/income-poverty/poverty/guidance/poverty-measures.html' target='_blank'>national benchmark</a> used to estimate how many people lack enough income to meet basic needs. Because the threshold is the same for the entire country, official counts tend to underestimate poverty in high-cost places like Washington, DC. Though far from perfect, the poverty rate lets us compare the prosperity of people and places.</p><p><a href='https://www.urban.org/features/understanding-poverty' target='_blank'>People below poverty</a> can face severe hardships including homelessness, illness, and hunger. Neighborhoods with <a href='https://www.urban.org/research/publication/concentrated-poverty-and-regional-equity' target='_blank'>high poverty rates</a> tend to suffer from other inequitable conditions, such as higher shares of people who lack jobs and educational opportunities.</p><p>Lifting people above poverty requires removing structural barriers that have created inequities in society and forced people into hardship and helping people overcome personal challenges. Strategies include <a href='https://www.mobilitypartnership.org/imagining-future-work-fosters-mobility-all' target='_blank'>extending basic protections to all workers</a>, <a href='https://www.urban.org/research/publication/nature-work-and-social-safety-net' target='_blank'>strengthening the social safety net</a> for those who cannot work, and providing <<a href='https://www.urban.org/workforce-development-systems-and-programs' target='_blank'>training programs</a> to help those who can work get and keep higher-paying jobs in the modern workforce.</p>",
  "Children above poverty": "<p>The <a href='https://www.census.gov/topics/income-poverty/poverty/guidance/poverty-measures.html' target='_blank'>poverty threshold</a> is a <a href='https://www.census.gov/topics/income-poverty/poverty/guidance/poverty-measures.html' target='_blank'>national benchmark</a> used to estimate how many people lack enough income to meet basic needs. Because the threshold is the same for the entire country, official counts tend to underestimate poverty in high-cost places like Washington, DC. Though far from perfect, the poverty rate lets us compare the prosperity of people and places.</p><p><a href='http://www.nccp.org/topics/childpoverty.html' target='_blank'>Children below poverty</a> are <a href='https://nyaspubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1196/annals.1425.023' target='_blank'>less likely to do well</a> and <a href='http://www.ascd.org/publications/educational-leadership/may13/vol70/num08/How-Poverty-Affects-Classroom-Engagement.aspx' target='_blank'>be engaged</a> in school. Children in families with low incomes are more likely to <a href='http://pediatrics.aappublications.org/content/112/Supplement_3/707' target='_blank'>suffer from poor health</a>. <a href='https://datacenter.kidscount.org/data/tables/6795-children-living-in-areas-of-concentrated-poverty#detailed/2/10/false/1607,1572,1485,1376,1201,1074,880,11/any/13891,13892' target='_blank'>One in four children in DC</a> live in <a href='https://www.urban.org/research/publication/concentrated-poverty-and-regional-equity' target='_blank'>neighborhoods with high poverty rates</a>, which tend to suffer from other inequitable conditions, such as higher shares of people who lack jobs and educational opportunities.</p><p>Lifting people above poverty requires removing structural barriers that have created inequities in society and forced people into hardship and helping people overcome personal challenges. Strategies include <a href='https://www.mobilitypartnership.org/imagining-